      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Application Scenarios</h2>
        <div class="scenario-list">
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>LCM Pre-Bonding Surface Preparation</h3>
            <p>Liquid crystal modules require clean, charge-free surfaces before polarizer lamination, FPC bonding, and backlight assembly. Any particle trapped between the polarizer and glass panel creates a permanent bright spot defect visible to the end user. The LCM Series cleaner removes particles and neutralizes static before each critical bonding step, reducing the defect rate at final inspection.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>High-Throughput LCM Production Lines</h3>
            <p>With throughput up to 1 piece per second, the LCM Series is designed to keep pace with high-volume display manufacturing without becoming a production bottleneck. The fully sealed patent magnetic levitation drive system ensures consistent cleaning performance at production speed without generating particles from the drive mechanism itself.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Pre-Final Assembly Quality Gate</h3>
            <p>Before an LCM module is committed to final product assembly — whether in a smartphone, tablet, monitor, or industrial display — a final cleaning pass removes any contamination accumulated during the assembly process. The LCM Series provides this final contamination gate, supported by professional sensors for variable speed control that adapts to different module sizes and handling requirements.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Key Technology: Fully Sealed Magnetic Levitation Drive</h2>
        <p>Conventional roller bearing drives generate wear particles over time — an invisible contamination source that directly undermines the cleaning process. The LCM Series uses a fully sealed magnetic levitation drive with patent protection, producing zero friction particles at any production speed. The sealed enclosure also protects the drive mechanism from the particle-laden environment of display manufacturing, extending service life significantly compared to open-bearing systems.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block faq-block">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What types of LCM modules can this machine clean?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The LCM Series handles liquid crystal modules across a range of sizes used in smartphones, tablets, monitors, automotive displays, and industrial panels. Module size compatibility and cleaning width are configured to your production specification.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What throughput can the LCM Series achieve?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The LCM Series supports throughput up to 1 piece per second with professional sensors for speed control, making it suitable for high-volume display manufacturing production lines.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What is a 'fully sealed patent design' magnetic levitation drive?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The fully sealed magnetic levitation drive eliminates mechanical bearings entirely, so the drive system generates no wear particles. The sealed enclosure protects internal components from the production environment. This patented design is critical in LCM manufacturing, where any particle source in the cleaning machine itself defeats the purpose of cleaning.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Can the machine handle different LCM module thicknesses?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. The variable speed control system with professional sensors adapts to modules of different sizes and thicknesses. Specific accommodation ranges are confirmed during specification review.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Does the LCM cleaner include static elimination?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. Full particle and static protection is integrated, neutralizing electrostatic charge on module surfaces simultaneously with particle removal to prevent re-contamination after cleaning.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How is the LCM Series different from the optical film or polarizer cleaning machines?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The LCM Series is optimized for rigid and semi-rigid liquid crystal module assemblies, with throughput up to 1 piece per second. The optical film cleaner handles large-format flexible film rolls and sheets, while the polarizer cleaner is specialized for precision cleaning of individual polarizer films before lamination. Contact us if you need help selecting the right machine for your specific substrate and process stage.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

